cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on HTTP Adaptive Streaming (HAS) techniques for video delivery in mobile networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper evaluates the performance of HAS algorithms in terms of user quality-of-experience (QoE) for video streaming. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the impact of network characteristics on QoE. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the information and data transmission aspects of HAS algorithms. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely possibility as the paper does not seem to focus on security aspects of video streaming.
